msgid "<emphasis>CULTURE</emphasis> <acronym>RTFM</acronym>"
msgstr "<emphasis>VĂN HÓA</emphasis> <acronym>HÃY ĐỌC TÀI LIỆU ĐI (RTFM)</acronym>"

msgid "<primary><acronym>RTFM</acronym></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><acronym>HÃY ĐỌC TÀI LIỆU ĐI (RTFM)</acronym></primary>"

msgid "This acronym stands for “Read the F***ing Manual”, but can also be expanded in a friendlier variant, “Read the Fine Manual”. This phrase is sometimes used in (terse) responses to questions from newbies. It is rather abrupt, and betrays a certain annoyance at a question asked by someone who has not even bothered to read the documentation. Some say that this classic response is better than no response at all (since it indicates that the documentation contains the information sought), or than a more verbose and angry answer."
msgstr "Từ viết tắt này đại diện cho cụm từ “Hãy đọc tài liệu đi (Read the F***ing Manual)”, nhưng cũng có thể mở rộng ra thành một phiên bản thân thiện hơn, “Xin Hãy Đọc Tài liệu Kĩ Càng hơn(Read the Fine Manual)”. Cụm từ này thỉnh thoảng được sử dụng trong các câu trả lời (ngắn gọn) cho các câu hỏi của những người mới bắt đầu. Nó khá là ngắn, và thể hiện một cảm giác phiền phức với một câu hỏi được hỏi bởi một người không chịu để tâm đến việc đọc tài liệu hướng dẫn. Một số nói rằng câu trả lời kinh điển này tốt hơn là không có câu trả lời nào (bởi nó cho thấy rằng tài liệu hướng dẫn có chứa thông tin cần tìm), hoặc tốt hơn một câu trả lời dài dòng và đầy sự giận dữ."

msgid "In any case, if someone responds “RTFM” to you, it is often wise not to take offense. Since this answer may be perceived as vexing, you might want to try and avoid receiving it. If the information that you need is not in the manual, which can happen, you might want to say so, preferably in your initial question. You should also describe the various steps that you have personally taken to find information before you raised a question on a forum. Following Eric Raymond's guidelines is a good way to avoid the most common mistakes and get useful answers. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://catb.org/~esr/faqs/smart-questions.html\" />"
msgstr "Trong bất cứ trường hợp nào, nếu một người nào đó trả lời “RTFM” với bạn, sẽ tốt hơn nếu bạn đừng coi đó là xúc phạm. Bởi câu trả lời này thường bị xem là dễ gây ra sự tức giận, bạn có thể muốn cố gắng tránh nhận câu trả lời này. Nếu thông tin bạn cần không có trong hướng dẫn sử dụng, vốn có thể xảy ra, bạn có thể muốn nói ra điều đó, và thực sự nên làm điều đó trong câu hỏi đầu tiên của bạn. Bạn cũng nên mô tả các bước bạn đã một mình thử để tìm thông tin trước khi bạn đưa ra một câu hỏi trên một diễn đàn. Tuân thủ theo các hướng dẫn của Eric Raymon là một cách tốt để tránh các sai lầm thường gặp phải và nhận được các câu trả lời hữu dụng. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://catb.org/~esr/faqs/smart-questions.html\" />"

msgid "Manual pages, while relatively terse in style, contain a great deal of essential information. We will quickly go over the command for viewing them. Simply type <command>man <replaceable>manual-page</replaceable></command> — the manual page usually goes by the same name as the command whose documentation is sought. For example, to learn about the possible options for the <command>cp</command> command, you would type the <command>man cp</command> command at the shell prompt (see sidebar <xref linkend=\"sidebar.shell\" />)."
msgstr "Các trang hướng dẫn sử dựng, mặc dù có phong cách khá ngắn gọn, nhưng chứa rất nhiều thông tin. Chúng ta sẽ đi nhanh qua lệnh này để xem chúng. Đơn giản chỉ nhập <command>man <replaceable>trang-hướng-dẫn</replaceable></command> — trang hướng dẫn sử dụng thường có cùng tên với lệnh mà chúng ta cần tìm hướng dẫn. Ví dụ, để tìm các lựa chọn cho lệnh <command>cp</command>, bạn sẽ nhập lệnh <command>man cp</command> ở dòng lệnh (xem <xref linkend=\"sidebar.shell\" />)."

msgid "<emphasis>BACK TO BASICS</emphasis> The shell, a command line interpreter"
msgstr "<emphasis>TRỞ VỀ CƠ BẢN</emphasis> Shell, một trình phiên dịch dòng lệnh"

msgid "<primary>command line interpreter</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>trình phiên dịch dòng lệnh</primary>"

msgid "<primary>shell</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>shell</primary>"

msgid "A command line interpreter, also called a “shell”, is a program that executes commands that are either entered by the user or stored in a script. In interactive mode, it displays a prompt (usually ending in <literal>$</literal> for a normal user, or by <literal>#</literal> for an administrator) indicating that it is ready to read a new command. <xref linkend=\"short-remedial-course\" /> describes the basics of using the shell."
msgstr "Một trình biên dịch dòng lệnh, cũng được gọi là “shell”, là một chương trình chạy các lệnh được nhập bởi người sử dụng hoặc được lưu sẵn trong một tập tin kịch bản. Trong chế độ tương tác trực tiếp, nó hiển thị một cụm từ nhắc (thường kết thúc bằng <literal>$</literal> cho một người sử dụng bình thường, hoặc bằng <literal>#</literal> cho một quản trị viên) cho biết rằng nó đã sẵn sàng để đọc vào một lệnh mới. <xref linkend=\"short-remedial-course\" /> mô tả những cơ bản của việc sử dụng shell."

msgid "The default and most commonly used shell is <command>bash</command> (Bourne Again SHell), but there are others, including <command>dash</command>, <command>csh</command>, <command>tcsh</command> and <command>zsh</command>."
msgstr "Shell ngầm định được sử dụng nhiều nhất là <command>bash</command> (Bourne Again SHell), nhưng cũng có những công cụ khác, bao gồm <command>dash</command>, <command>csh</command>, <command>tcsh</command> và <command>zsh</command>."

msgid "Among other things, most shells offer help during input at the prompt, such as the completion of command or file names (which you can generally activate by pressing the <keycap>tab</keycap> key), or recalling previous commands (history management)."
msgstr "Trong những thứ khác, đa phần các shell hỗ trợ giúp đỡ trong lúc nhập ở dòng lệnh, ví dụ như tự động hoàn tất lệnh hoặc các tên tập tin (vốn bạn có thể kích hoạt bởi nhấn nút <keycap>tab</keycap>), hoặc gọi lại các lệnh trước đó (quản lý lịch sử)."

msgid "Man pages not only document programs accessible from the command line, but also configuration files, system calls, C library functions, and so forth. Sometimes names can collide. For example, the shell's <command>read</command> command has the same name as the <function>read</function> system call. This is why manual pages are organized in numbered sections:"
msgstr "Các trang hướng dẫn sử dụng không chỉ hướng dẫn các chương trình truy cập được từ dòng lệnh mà còn các tập tin cấu hình, các lệnh gọi hệ thống, các hàm số thư viện của C, và vâng vâng. Thỉnh thoảng tên có thể trùng lặp. Ví dụ, lệnh <command>read</command> của shell có cùng tên với lệnh gọi hệ thống <function>read</function>. Đó là lý do tại sao các trang hướng dẫn sử dụng được cấu trúc theo các phần được đánh số:"

msgid "commands that can be executed from the command line;"
msgstr "các lệnh có thể được chạy từ dòng lệnh"

msgid "system calls (functions provided by the kernel);"
msgstr "các lệnh gọi hệ thống (các hàm được cung cấp bởi nhân (kernel));"

msgid "library functions (provided by system libraries);"
msgstr "các hàm thư viện (được cung cấp bởi các thư viện hệ thống);"

msgid "devices (on Unix-like systems, these are special files, usually placed in the <filename>/dev/</filename> directory);"
msgstr "các thiết bị (trên các hệ thống giống Unix, chúng là những tập tin đặc biệt, thường được đặt trong thư mục <filename>/dev/</filename>);"

msgid "configuration files (formats and conventions);"
msgstr "các tập tin cấu hình (các định dạng và quy tắc truyền thống);"

msgid "games;"
msgstr "các trò chơi;"

msgid "sets of macros and standards;"
msgstr "các tập hợp macro và các tiêu chuẩn"

msgid "system administration commands;"
msgstr "các lệnh quản lý hệ thống"

msgid "kernel routines."
msgstr "các tập lệnh của nhân"

msgid "It is possible to specify the section of the manual page that you are looking for: to view the documentation for the <function>read</function> system call, you would type <command>man 2 read</command>. When no section is explicitly specified, the first section that has a manual page with the requested name will be shown. Thus, <command>man shadow</command> returns <citerefentry><refentrytitle>shadow</refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry> because there are no manual pages for <foreignphrase>shadow</foreignphrase> in sections 1 to 4."
msgstr "Ta có thể chỉ định phần cho trang hướng dẫn ta đang tìm: để xem tài liệu hướng dẫn cho lệnh gọi hệ thống <function>read</function>, bạn có thể nhập <command>man 2 read</command>. Khi không có phần nào được chỉ định công khai, phần đầu tiên có một trang hướng dẫn sử dụng với tên trùng sẽ được hiển thị. Vì thế, <command>man shadow</command> trả về <citerefentry><refentrytitle>shadow</refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry> bởi vì không có trang hướng dẫn sử dụng nào cho <foreignphrase>shadow</foreignphrase> trong phần 1 tới phần 4."

msgid "<emphasis>TIP</emphasis> <command>whatis</command>"
msgstr "<emphasis>MẸO</emphasis> <command>whatis</command>"

msgid "<primary><command>whatis</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>whatis</command></primary>"

msgid "If you do not want to look at the full manual page, but only a short description to confirm that it is what you are looking for, simply enter <command>whatis <replaceable>command</replaceable></command>."
msgstr "Nếu bạn không muốn đọc hết trang hướng dẫn, nhưng chỉ muốn một mô tả ngắn gọn để xác nhận rằng đó là thứ mình cần tìm, hãy đơn giản nhập <command>whatis <replaceable>command</replaceable></command>."

msgid ""
"\n"
"<computeroutput>$ </computeroutput><userinput>whatis scp</userinput>\n"
"<computeroutput>scp (1)     - secure copy (remote file copy program)</computeroutput>"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<computeroutput>$ </computeroutput><userinput>whatis scp</userinput>\n"
"<computeroutput>scp (1)     - secure copy (remote file copy program)</computeroutput>"

msgid "This short description is included in the <emphasis>NAME</emphasis> section at the beginning of all manual pages."
msgstr "Phần mô tả ngắn gọn sau được đính kèm trong phần <emphasis>NAME</emphasis> ở đoạn đầu của tất cả các trang hướng dẫn sử dụng."

msgid "Of course, if you do not know the names of the commands, the manual is not going to be of much use to you. This is the purpose of the <command>apropos</command> command, which helps you conduct a search in the manual pages, or more specifically in their short descriptions. Each manual page begins essentially with a one line summary. <command>apropos</command> returns a list of manual pages whose summary mentions the requested keyword(s). If you choose them well, you will find the name of the command that you need."
msgstr "Dĩ nhiên, nếu bạn không muốn biết những tên của các lệnh, hướng dẫn sử dụng sẽ không có ít gì. Đây là mục đích của lệnh <command>apropos</command>, vốn giúp bạn thực hiện một lệnh tìm kiếm trong các trang hướng dẫn sử dụng, hoặc cụ thể hơn trong các mô tả ngắn gọn của chúng. Mỗi một trang hướng dẫn sử dụng bắt đầu bằng một bản tóm tắt có độ dài một dòng. <command>apropos</command> trả về một danh sách các trang hướng dẫn sử dụng mà bản hướng dẫn của chúng có đề cập đến (các) từ khóa. Nếu bạn chọn từ khóa tốt, bạn sẽ tìm thấy tên của lệnh bạn cần."

msgid "Finding <command>cp</command> with <command>apropos</command>"
msgstr "Tìm kiếm <command>cp</command> với <command>apropos</command>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"<computeroutput>$ </computeroutput><userinput>apropos \"copy file\"</userinput>\n"
"<computeroutput>cp (1)               - copy files and directories\n"
"cpio (1)             - copy files to and from archives\n"
"gvfs-copy (1)        - Copy files\n"
"gvfs-move (1)        - Copy files\n"
"hcopy (1)            - copy files from or to an HFS volume\n"
"install (1)          - copy files and set attributes\n"
"ntfscp (8)           - copy file to an NTFS volume.\n"
"</computeroutput>"
