msgid "<emphasis>TIP</emphasis> Browsing by following links"
msgstr "<emphasis>MẸO</emphasis> Duyệt bằng cách đi theo các đường dẫn (đường link)"

msgid "Many manual pages have a “SEE ALSO” section, usually at the end. It refers to other manual pages relevant to similar commands, or to external documentation. In this way, it is possible to find relevant documentation even when the first choice is not optimal."
msgstr "Nhiều trang hướng dẫn có một phần “SEE ALSO”, vốn nằm ở cuối. Chúng thường nói về các trang hướng dẫn khác liên quan đến các lệnh tương tự, hoặc về các tài liệu hướng dẫn bên ngoài. Bằng cách này, ta có thể tìm nhiều tài liệu hướng dẫn có liên quan hơn thậm chí khi lựa chọn tìm kiếm đầu tiên không tối ưu."

msgid "The <command>man</command> command is not the only means of consulting the manual pages, since <command>konqueror</command> (in KDE) and <command>yelp</command> (under GNOME) programs also offer this possibility. There is also a web interface, provided by the <command>man2html</command> package, which allows you to view manual pages in a web browser. On a computer where this package is installed, use this URL: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://localhost/cgi-bin/man/man2html\" />"
msgstr "Lệnh <command>man</command> không chỉ là cách duy nhất để tra cứu các trang hướng dẫn, bởi các chương trình <command>konqueror</command> (trong KDE) và <command>yelp</command> (trong GNOME) cũng cho phép khả năng này. Cũng có một giao diện web, được cung cấp bởi gói phần mềm <command>man2html</command>, vốn cho phép bạn xem các trang hướng dẫn sử dụng trên một trình duyệt. Trên một máy tính nơi mà gói phần mềm được cài đặt, sử dụng đường dẫn trang web sau: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://localhost/cgi-bin/man/man2html\" />"

msgid "This utility requires a web server. This is why you should choose to install this package on one of your servers: all users of the local network could benefit from this service (including non-Linux machines), and this will allow you not to set up an HTTP server on each workstation. If your server is also accessible from other networks, it may be desirable to restrict access to this service only to users of the local network."
msgstr "Tiện ích này buộc phải có một máy phục vụ web. Đây là lý do tại sao bạn nên chọn cài đặt một gói phần mềm trên một trong các máy phục vụ của bạn: tất cả các người sử dụng của mạng nội bộ có thể có lợi được từ dịch vụ này (bao gồm cả các máy tính không phải Linux), và điều này sẽ cho phép bạn không cần cài đặt một máy phục vụ HTTP trên mỗi máy trạm. Nếu máy phục vụ của bạn có thể truy cập được từ các mạng khác, bạn có thể muốn giới hạn truy cập đến dịch vụ này với những người sử dụng của mạng nội bộ."

msgid "<primary><command>man2html</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>man2html</command></primary>"

msgid "<emphasis>DEBIAN POLICY</emphasis> Required man pages"
msgstr "<emphasis>CHÍNH SÁCH DEBIAN</emphasis> Các trang hướng dẫn sử dụng cần thiết"

msgid "Debian requires each program to have a manual page. If the upstream author does not provide one, the Debian package maintainer will usually write a minimal page that will at the very least direct the reader to the location of the original documentation."
msgstr "Debian buộc mỗi chương trình phải có một trang hướng dẫn sử dụng. Nếu tác giả thượng nguồn không cung cấp nó, nhà bảo trì gói phần mềm Debian sẽ thông thường viết một trang hướng dẫn tối thiểu vốn sẽ ít nhất dẫn người đọc đến nơi của tài liệu hướng dẫn nguyên gốc."

msgid "<emphasis>info</emphasis> Documents"
msgstr "Các tài liệu <emphasis>info</emphasis>"

msgid "<primary><emphasis>info</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis>info</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "<primary>GNU</primary><secondary>Info</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>GNU</primary><secondary>Info</secondary>"

msgid "The GNU project has written manuals for most of its programs in the <emphasis>info</emphasis> format; this is why many manual pages refer to the corresponding <emphasis>info</emphasis> documentation. This format offers some advantages, but the default program to view these documents (it is called <command>info</command>) is also slightly more complex. You would be well advised to use <command>pinfo</command> instead (from the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">pinfo</emphasis> package)."
msgstr "Dự án GNU đã viết các tài liệu hướng dẫn cho đa số chương trình của nó dưới định dạng <emphasis>info</emphasis>; đó là lý do nhiều trang hướng dẫn sử dụng chỉ đến các tài liệu hướng dẫn <emphasis>info</emphasis>. Định dạng này có một vài ưu điểm, nhưng chương trình ngầm định để xem các tài liệu này (nó được gọi là <command>info</command>) thì có một chút phức tạp hơn. Thay vào đó, bạn được khuyên hãy sử dụng <command>pinfo</command> (từ gói phần mềm <emphasis role=\"pkg\">pinfo</emphasis>)."

msgid "<primary><command>pinfo</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>pinfo</command></primary>"

msgid "The <emphasis>info</emphasis> documentation has a hierarchical structure, and if you invoke <command>pinfo</command> without parameters, it will display a list of the nodes available at the first level. Usually, nodes bear the name of the corresponding commands."
msgstr "Tài liệu hướng dẫn <emphasis>info</emphasis> có một cấu trúc tầng lớp, và nếu bạn chạy <command>pinfo</command> mà không có tham số, nó sẽ hiển thị một danh sách các nút có sẵn ở tầng đầu tiên. Thông thường, các nút mang tên của các lệnh tương ứng."

msgid "With <command>pinfo</command> navigating between these nodes is easy to achieve with the arrow keys. Alternatively, you could also use a graphical browser, which is a lot more user-friendly. Again, <command>konqueror</command> and <command>yelp</command> work; the <command>info2www</command> also provides a web interface. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://localhost/cgi-bin/info2www\" />"
msgstr "Với <command>pinfo</command> việc di chuyển giữa các nút này là dễ thực hiện được với các phím mũi tên. Ngoài ra, bạn cũng có thể sử dụng một trình duyệt đồ họa, vốn thân thiện với người sử dụng hơn rất nhiều. Một lần nữa, <command>konqueror</command> và <command>yelp</command> đều hoạt động tốt; <command>info2www</command> cũng cung cấp một giao diện web. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://localhost/cgi-bin/info2www\" />"

msgid "<primary><command>info2www</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>info2www</command></primary>"

msgid "Note that the <emphasis>info</emphasis> system is not suitable for translation, unlike the <command>man</command> page system. <emphasis>info</emphasis> documents are thus almost always in English. However, when you ask the <command>pinfo</command> program to display a non-existing <emphasis>info</emphasis> page, it will fall back on the <emphasis>man</emphasis> page by the same name (if it exists), which might be translated."
msgstr "Ghi chú rằng hệ thống <emphasis>info</emphasis> không phù hợp cho việc phiên dịch, không giống như hệ thống trang <command>man</command>. Các tài liệu <emphasis>info</emphasis> vì thế luôn ở dưới dạng tiếng Anh. Tuy nhiên, nếu bạn yêu cầu chương trình <command>pinfo</command> hiển thị một trang <emphasis>info</emphasis> không có tồn tại, nó sẽ lui về trang <emphasis>man</emphasis> có cùng tên (nếu nó tồn tại), vốn có thể phiên dịch được. "

msgid "Specific Documentation"
msgstr "Tài liệu hướng dẫn cụ thể"

msgid "Each package includes its own documentation. Even the least well documented programs generally have a <filename>README</filename> file containing some interesting and/or important information. This documentation is installed in the <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>package</replaceable>/</filename> directory (where <replaceable>package</replaceable> represents the name of the package). If the documentation is particularly large, it may not be included in the program's main package, but might be offloaded to a dedicated package which is usually named <literal><replaceable>package</replaceable>-doc</literal>. The main package generally recommends the documentation package so that you can easily find it."
msgstr "Mỗi gói phần mềm bao gồm tài liệu hướng dẫn của chính nó. Thậm chí các chương trình được hướng dẫn ít chi tiết nhất nhìn chung có một tập tin <filename>README</filename> chứa một vài thông tin thú vị và/hoặc quan trọng. Tài liệu này được cài đặt vào thư mục <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>gói-phần-mềm</replaceable>/</filename> (trong đó <replaceable>gói-phần-mềm</replaceable> đại diện cho tên của gói phần mềm). Nếu tài liệu hướng dẫn cực kỳ lớn, nó có thể không được đính kèm trong gói phần mềm chính của chương trình đó, nhưng có thể được giảm tải sang một gói phần mềm chỉ dành cho nó vốn thường được đặt tên <literal><replaceable>gói-phần-mềm</replaceable>-doc</literal>. Gói phần mềm chính thường để cử một gói phần mềm hướng dẫn sử dụng để bạn có thể dễ dàng tìm thấy nó."

msgid "<primary><filename>README.Debian</filename></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>README.Debian</filename></primary>"

msgid "<primary><filename>changelog.Debian.gz</filename></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>changelog.Debian.gz</filename></primary>"

msgid "<primary><filename>NEWS.Debian.gz</filename></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>NEWS.Debian.gz</filename></primary>"

msgid "The <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>package</replaceable>/</filename> directory also contains some files provided by Debian which complete the documentation by specifying the package's particularities or improvements compared to a traditional installation of the software. The <filename>README.Debian</filename> file also indicates all of the adaptations that were made to comply with the Debian Policy. The <filename>changelog.Debian.gz</filename> file allows the user to follow the modifications made to the package over time: it is very useful to try to understand what has changed between two installed versions that do not have the same behavior. Finally, there is sometimes a <filename>NEWS.Debian.gz</filename> file which documents the major changes in the program that may directly concern the administrator."
msgstr "Thư mục <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>gói-phần-mềm</replaceable>/</filename> cũng chứa một vài tập tin cung cấp bởi Debian vốn hoàn thiện tài liệu hướng dẫn bằng cách chỉ ra những điểm lạ thường của gói phần mềm hoặc các cải tiến so với bản cài đặt bình thường của phần mềm. Tập tin <filename>README.Debian</filename> cũng chỉ ra tất cả các thay đổi để thích ứng đã được tạo ra để tuân thủ chính sách Debian. Tập tin <filename>changelog.Debian.gz</filename> cho phép người sử dụng theo dõi các thay đổi xảy ra với gói phần mềm theo thời gian: điều đó rất tiện cho những ai cố gắng hiểu điều gì đã xảy ra giữa hai phiên bản đã được cài đặt mà không có cùng một hành vi giống nhau. Cuối cùng, thỉnh thoảng cũng có một tập tin <filename>NEWS.Debian.gz</filename> vốn ghi lại những thay đổi chính thức với chương trình vốn có thể làm cho quản trị viên lo ngại."

msgid "Websites"
msgstr "Các trang thông tin điện tử (Website)"

msgid "In most cases, free software programs have websites that are used to distribute it and to bring together the community of its developers and users. These sites are frequently loaded with relevant information in various forms: official documentation, FAQ (Frequently Asked Questions), mailing list archives, etc. Problems that you may encounter have often already been the subject of many questions; the FAQ or mailing list archives may have a solution for it. A good mastery of search engines will prove immensely valuable to find relevant pages quickly (by restricting the search to the Internet domain or sub-domain dedicated to the program). If the search returns too many pages or if the results do not match what you seek, you can add the keyword <userinput>debian</userinput> to limit results and target relevant information."
msgstr "Trong đa số các trường hợp, các chương trình phần mềm nguồn mở có các trang thông tin điện tử vốn được sử dụng để phân phối các phần mềm đó và để tạo một cộng đồng cho những nhà phát triển và những người sử dụng. Những trang này thường chứa những thông tin liên quan trọng dưới các hình thức khác nhau: tài liệu hướng dẫn chính thức, FAQ (Các câu hỏi thường gặp - Frequently Asked Questions), các kho lưu trữ bó thư điện tử, vâng vâng. Các vấn đề bạn có thể gặp thường đã là chủ đề của nhiều câu hỏi trước đây; FAQ hoặc các kho lưu trữ bó thư điện tử thường có một giải pháp cho nó. Làm chủ các bộ máy tìm kiếm sẽ trở nên vô cùng giá trị trong việc tìm kiếm các trang thông tin liên quan một cách nhanh chóng (bằng việc giới hạn tìm kiếm xuống những miền Internet hoặc các miền phụ chỉ dành cho chương trình đó). Nếu tìm kiếm trả về quá nhiều trang hoặc nếu các kết quả không khớp với cái bạn tìm kiếm, bạn có thể thêm từ khóa <userinput>debian</userinput> để giới hạn các kết quả và nhắm đến các thông tin có liên quan hơn."

msgid "<emphasis>TIPS</emphasis> From error to solution"
msgstr "<emphasis>MẸO</emphasis> Từ sự cố đến giải pháp"

msgid "If the software returns a very specific error message, enter it into the search engine (between double quotes, <literal>\"</literal>, in order to search not for individual keywords, but for the complete phrase). In most cases, the first links returned will contain the answer that you need."
msgstr "Nếu phần mềm trả về một thông điệp lỗi rất cụ thể, hãy nhập nó vào bộ máy tìm kiếm (giữa các dấu nháy đôi, <literal>\"</literal>, để tìm kiếm không chỉ từng từ khóa, mà cả cụm từ khóa). Trong đa số các trường hợp, những kết quả đầu tiên sẽ chứa câu trả lời mà bạn cần."

msgid "In other cases, you will get very general errors, such as “Permission denied”. In this case, it is best to check the permissions of the elements involved (files, user ID, groups, etc.)."
msgstr "Trong các trường hợp khác, bạn có nhận được các lỗi rất chung chung, như là “Permission denied(Không được phép)”. Trong trường hợp này, tốt nhất hãy kiểm tra các quyền cho phép của những thành phần có liên quan (các tập tin, ID người sử dụng, các nhóm, vâng vâng)."

msgid "If you do not know the address for the software's website, there are various means of getting it. First, check if there is a <literal>Homepage</literal> field in the package's meta-information (<command>apt-cache show <replaceable>package</replaceable></command>). Alternately, the package description may contain a link to the program's official website. If no URL is indicated, look at <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>package</replaceable>/copyright</filename>. The Debian maintainer generally indicates in this file where they got the program's source code, and this is likely to be the website that you need to find. If at this stage your search is still unfruitful, consult a free software directory, such as FSF's Free Software Directory, or search directly with a search engine, such as Google, DuckDuckGo, Yahoo, etc. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"https://directory.fsf.org/wiki/Main_Page\" />"
msgstr "Nếu bạn không biết địa chỉ của trang web của phần mềm đó, có vài cách để tìm thấy nó. Đầu tiên, kiểm tra xem có một trường <literal>Homepage</literal> trong thông tin phụ về gói phần mềm đó hay không (<command>apt-cache show <replaceable>gói-phần-mềm</replaceable></command>). Ngoài ra, bản mô tả của gói phần mềm có thể chứa một đường dẫn tới trang thông tin điện tử chính thức của chương trình. Nếu không có đường dẫn nào được tìm thấy, hãy nhìn vào <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>gói-phần-mềm</replaceable>/copyright</filename>. Nhà bảo trì Debian thông thường sẽ chỉ ra trong tập tin này từ đâu họ có được mã nguồn, và đó có thể là trang web bạn cần tìm. Nếu tại bước này tìm kiếm của bạn vẫn chưa có kết quả, hãy tham khảo danh bạ phần mềm tự do, như là Danh bạ Phần mềm Tự do của FSF, hoặc tìm kiếm trực tiếp với một bộ máy tìm kiếm, như là Google, DuckDuckGo, Yahoo, vâng vâng. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"https://directory.fsf.org/wiki/Main_Page\" />"

msgid "<primary><filename>copyright</filename></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>copyright</filename></primary>"

msgid "<primary>Free Software Directory</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Danh bạ Phần mềm Tự do (Free Software Directory)</primary>"

msgid "You might also want to check the Debian wiki, a collaborative website where anybody, even simple visitors, can make suggestions directly from their browsers. It is used equally by developers who design and specify their projects, and by users who share their knowledge by writing documents collaboratively. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://wiki.debian.org/\" />"
msgstr "Bạn có thể muốn nhìn qua bách khoa toàn thư Debian, một trang web cho phép làm việc với nhau nơi mà bất cứ ai, thậm chí những vị khách, có thể đóng góp gợi ý trực tiếp từ trình duyệt của họ. Nó được sử dụng như nhau bởi các nhà phát triển thiết kế và soạn thảo chi tiết kỹ thuật cho các dự án của họ, và bởi những người sử dụng chia sẻ kiến thức của họ bằng việc phối hợp soạn thảo các tài liệu hướng dẫn. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://wiki.debian.org/\" />"

msgid "<primary><emphasis>wiki.debian.org</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis>wiki.debian.org</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "Tutorials (<emphasis>HOWTO</emphasis>)"
msgstr "Hướng dẫn từng bước (<emphasis>HOWTO</emphasis>)"

msgid "<primary><emphasis>HOWTO</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis>HOWTO</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "A howto is a document that describes, in concrete terms and step by step, “how to” reach a predefined goal. The covered goals are relatively varied, but often technical in nature: for example, setting up IP Masquerading, configuring software RAID, installing a Samba server, etc. These documents often attempt to cover all of the potential problems likely to occur during the implementation of a given technology."
msgstr "Một howto là một tài liệu mô tả, sử dụng các cụm từ dễ hiểu và từng bước một, “làm sao“ để đạt được một mục tiêu cho trước. Các mục tiêu được đề cập tương đối đa dạng, nhưng thông thường mang nặng tính kĩ thuật: ví dụ, cài đặt IP Masquerading, cấu hình RAID phần mềm, cài đặt một máy phục vụ Samba, vâng vâng. Những tài liệu này thường cố gắng bao phủ hết tất cả các vấn đề có thể xảy ra trong suốt quá trình hiện thực hóa một công nghệ cho trước."

msgid "Many such tutorials are managed by the Linux Documentation Project (LDP), whose website hosts all of these documents: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://www.tldp.org/\" />"
msgstr "Rất nhiều hướng dẫn từng bước như vậy được quản lý bởi Dự án Tài liệu Hướng dẫn Linux (Linux Documentation Project (LDP)). Trang thông tin điện tử của họ chứa tất cả những tài liệu này: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://www.tldp.org/\" />"

msgid "<primary>LDP</primary>"

msgstr "<primary>LDP</primary>"


msgid "<primary>Linux Documentation Project</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Dự án Tài liệu Hướng dẫn Linu(Linux Documentation Project)</primary>"

msgid "These documents should be taken with a grain of salt. They are often several years old; the information they contain is sometimes obsolete. This phenomenon is even more frequent for their translations, since updates are neither systematic nor instant after the publication of a new version of the original documents. This is part of the joys of working in a volunteer environment and without constraints…"
msgstr "Những tài liệu này nên được đọc cẩn thận. Chúng thường đã tồn tại một vài năm, thông tin chứa ở trong các tài liệu này thỉnh thoảng đã lỗi thời. Hiện tượng này thậm chí thường xuyên hơn với các bản dịch của chúng, bởi các cập nhật thường không có tính hệ thống và không tức thời sau lần xuất bản của phiên bản mới nhất của các tài liệu nguyên gốc. Đây là một phần của việc làm việc với môi trường tình nguyện và không có ràng buộc…"

msgid "Common Procedures"
msgstr "Các quy trình phổ biến"

msgid "<primary>standard procedure</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>quy trình chuẩn</primary>"

msgid "The purpose of this section is to present some general tips on certain operations that an administrator will frequently have to perform. These procedures will of course not cover every possible case in an exhaustive way, but they may serve as starting points for the more difficult cases."
msgstr "Mục đích của phần này là trình bày một vài mẹo chung cho một số tác vụ mà quản trị viên sẽ thường phải thực hiện. Các quy trình này sẽ dĩ nhiên không bao phủ từng ngóc ngách của tất cả các trường hợp có thể, nhưng chúng sẽ được sử dụng như những điểm bắt đầu cho các trường hợp khó hơn."

msgid "<emphasis>DISCOVERY</emphasis> Documentation in other languages"
msgstr "<emphasis>KHÁM PHÁ</emphasis> Tài liệu hướng dẫn theo các ngôn ngữ khác"

msgid "Often, documentation translated into a non-English language is available in a separate package with the name of the corresponding package, followed by <literal>-<replaceable>lang</replaceable></literal> (where <replaceable>lang</replaceable> is the two-letter ISO code for the language)."
msgstr "Thông thường, tài liệu hướng dẫn được dịch sang một ngôn ngữ không phải tiếng Anh sẽ có sẵn trong một gói phần mềm riêng biệt với tên của gói phần mềm tương ứng, theo sau bởi <literal>-<replaceable>lang</replaceable></literal> (trong đó <replaceable>lang</replaceable> là mã ISO 2 ký tự đại diện cho ngôn ngữ đó)."

msgid "For instance, the <emphasis>apt-howto-fr</emphasis> package contains the French translation of the howto for <emphasis>APT</emphasis>. Likewise, the <emphasis>quick-reference-fr</emphasis> and <emphasis>debian-reference-fr</emphasis> packages are the French versions of the reference guides for Debian (initially written in English by Osamu Aoki)."
msgstr "Ví dụ, gói phần mềm <emphasis>apt-howto-fr</emphasis> chứa bản dịch tiếng Pháp của <emphasis>APT</emphasis>. Tương tự, các gói phần mềm <emphasis>quick-reference-fr</emphasis> và <emphasis>debian-reference-fr</emphasis> là các phiên bản tiếng Pháp của các tài liệu tham khảo cho Debian (ban đầu được viết theo tiếng Anh bởi Osamu Aoki)."

msgid "Configuring a Program"
msgstr "Cấu hình một chương trình"

msgid "<primary>configuration</primary><secondary>program configuration</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>cấu hình</primary><secondary>cấu hình chương trình</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>program</primary><secondary>configuration</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>chương trình</primary><secondary>cấu hình</secondary>"

msgid "When you want to configure an unknown package, you must proceed in stages. First, you should read what the package maintainer has documented. Reading <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>package</replaceable>/README.Debian</filename> will indeed allow you to learn of specific provisions made to simplify the use of the software. It is sometimes essential in order to understand the differences from the original behavior of the program, as described in the general documentation, such as howtos. Sometimes this file also details the most common errors in order for you to avoid wasting time on common problems."
msgstr "Khi bạn muốn cấu hình một gói lạ, bạn nên đi từng bước một. Trước tiên, bạn nên đọc những gì đã được hướng dẫn bởi nhà bảo trì gói phần mềm đó. Đọc <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>package</replaceable>/README.Debian</filename> sẽ thực sự cho phép bạn biết những thứ được cung cấp sẵn để làm đơn giản việc sử dụng phần mềm. Điều này thỉnh thoảng rất quan trọng để hiểu được những sự khác biệt so với hành vi nguyên gốc, như được mô tả trong tài liệu hướng dẫn chung, như là các tài liệu hướng dẫn từng bước. Thỉnh thoảng tập tin này cũng đi sâu vào chi tiết những lỗi thường gặp để bạn có thể tránh mất thời gian vào các vấn đề này."

msgid "Then, you should look at the software's official documentation — refer to <xref linkend=\"sect.documentation-sources\" /> to identify the various existing documentation sources. The <command>dpkg -L <replaceable>package</replaceable></command> command gives a list of files included in the package; you can therefore quickly identify the available documentation (as well as the configuration files, located in <filename>/etc/</filename>). <command>dpkg -s <replaceable>package</replaceable></command> displays the package meta-data and shows any possible recommended or suggested packages; in there, you can find documentation or a utility that will ease the configuration of the software."
msgstr "Sau đó, bạn nên nhìn vào tài liệu hướng dẫn chính thức của phần mềm — hãy xem <xref linkend=\"sect.documentation-sources\" /> để nhận định được các nguồn tài liệu sẵn có. Lệnh <command>dpkg -L <replaceable>package</replaceable></command> trả về danh sách những tập tin được đính kèm trong gói phần mềm này; bạn có thể nhanh chóng nhận ra những tài liệu sẵn có (cũng như các tập tin cấu hình, nằm trong <filename>/etc/</filename>). Lệnh <command>dpkg -s <replaceable>package</replaceable></command> hiển thị những thông tin phụ của gói phần mềm và hiển thị bất kỳ các gói phần mềm được đề nghị hay gợi ý; ở trong đó, bạn có thể tìm thấy tài liệu hướng dẫn, hoặc một tiện ích vốn sẽ giúp giảm bớt khó khăn trong việc cấu hình phần mềm."

msgid "Finally, the configuration files are often self-documented by many explanatory comments detailing the various possible values for each configuration setting. So much so that it is sometimes enough to just choose a line to activate from among those available. In some cases, examples of configuration files are provided in the <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>package</replaceable>/examples/</filename> directory. They may serve as a basis for your own configuration file."
msgstr "Cuối cùng, các tập tin cấu hình thường có những dòng ghi chú đọc là hiểu giải thích các giá trị có thể có cho mỗi thiết lập cấu hình. Rất nhiều đến nỗi thỉnh thoảng chỉ cần chọn một dòng để kích hoạt giữa những thứ có sẵn là đủ. Trong một số trường hợp, các ví dụ về các tập tin cấu hình được cung cấp trong thư mục <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>package</replaceable>/examples/</filename>. Chúng có thể là cơ sở cho tập tin cấu hình của riêng bạn."

msgid "<emphasis>DEBIAN POLICY</emphasis> Location of examples"
msgstr "<emphasis>CHÍNH SÁCH DEBIAN</emphasis> Địa chỉ của các ví dụ"

msgid "<primary>examples, location</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>các ví dụ, địa chỉ</primary>"

msgid "All examples must be installed in the <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>package</replaceable>/examples/</filename> directory. This may be a configuration file, program source code (an example of the use of a library), or a data conversion script that the administrator can use in certain cases (such as to initialize a database). If the example is specific to a particular architecture, it should be installed in <filename>/usr/lib/<replaceable>package</replaceable>/examples/</filename> and there should be a link pointing to that file in the <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>package</replaceable>/examples/</filename> directory."
msgstr "Tất cả các ví dụ phải được cài đặt vào thư mục <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>gói-phần-mềm</replaceable>/examples/</filename>. Đây có thể là một tập tin cấu hình, mã nguồn chương trình (một ví dụ về cách sử dụng một thư viện) hoặc một kịch bản chuyển đổi dữ liệu mà quản trị viên có thể sử dụng trong một số trường hợp nhất định (như là khởi động một cơ sở dữ liệu). Nếu ví dụ đó chỉ liên quan tới một kiến trúc máy tính nào đó, nó nên được cài đặt vào <filename>/usr/lib/<replaceable>package</replaceable>/examples/</filename> và phải có một đường dẫn chỉ đến tập tin đó trong thư mục <filename>/usr/share/doc/<replaceable>gói-phần-mềm</replaceable>/examples/</filename>."

msgid "Monitoring What Daemons Are Doing"
msgstr "Theo dõi Hoạt động của Các dịch vụ nền"

msgid "Understanding what a daemon does is somewhat more complicated, since it does not interact directly with the administrator. To check that a daemon is actually working, you need to test it. For example, to check the Apache (web server) daemon, test it with an HTTP request."
msgstr "Hiểu những gì một dịch vụ chạy nền đang làm thì có một chút phức tạp, bởi nó không tương tác trực tiếp với quản trị viên. Để kiểm tra rằng một dịch vụ nền đang thực sự chạy, bạn cần phải kiểm tra nó. Ví dụ, để kiểm tra dịch vụ chạy nền Apache (máy phục vụ web), hãy kiểm tra nó với một yêu cầu HTTP."

msgid "To allow such tests, each daemon generally records everything that it does, as well as any errors that it encounters, in what are called “log files” or “system logs”. Logs are stored in <filename>/var/log/</filename> or one of its subdirectories. To know the precise name of a log file for each daemon, see its documentation. Note: a single test is not always sufficient if it does not cover all the possible usage cases; some problems only occur in particular circumstances."
msgstr "Để cho phép những bài kiểm tra đó, mỗi dịch vụ chạy nền nhìn chung ghi lại tất cả những gì nó làm, và cả những lỗi nó gặp phải, vào những thứ được gọi là “các tập tin nhật ký” hoặc “các nhật ký hệ thống”. Các nhật ký được lưu trong <filename>/var/log/</filename> hoặc một trong các thư mục con của nó. Để biết tên cụ thể của tập tin nhật ký của mỗi dịch vụ nền, hãy xem tài liệu hướng dẫn của nó. Chú ý: một bài kiểm tra luôn không đủ để bao phủ hết tất cả các trường hợp; một vài vấn đề chỉ xảy ra trong các trường hợp đặc biệt."

msgid "<emphasis>TOOL</emphasis> The <command>rsyslogd</command> daemon"
msgstr "<emphasis>CÔNG CỤ</emphasis> Dịch vụ nền <command>rsyslogd</command>"

msgid "<primary><command>syslogd</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>syslogd</command></primary>"

msgid "<primary>logs</primary><secondary>files</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>các nhật ký</primary><secondary>các tập tin</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>files</primary><secondary>logs</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>các tập tin</primary><secondary>các nhật ký</secondary>"

msgid "<command>rsyslogd</command> is special: it collects logs (internal system messages) that are sent to it by other programs. Each log entry is associated with a subsystem (e-mail, kernel, authentication, etc.) and a priority; <command>rsyslogd</command> processes these two pieces of information to decide on what to do. The log message may be recorded in various log files, and/or sent to an administration console. The details are defined in the <filename>/etc/rsyslog.conf</filename> configuration file (documented in the manual page of the same name)."
msgstr "<command>rsyslogd</command> rất đặc biệt: nó thu thập các thông điệp nhật ký (các thông điệp nội bộ hệ thống) vốn được gửi tới nó bởi các chương trình khác. Mỗi chỉ mục trong nhật ký được liên kết với một hệ thống nhỏ (thư điện tử, nhân(kernel), xác thực, vâng vâng) và một mức ưu tiên; <command>rsyslogd</command> xử lý hai mẩu thông tin này để quyết định phải làm gì. Thông điệp nhật ký có thể được lưu lại trong các tập tin nhật ký, và/hoặc gửi đến một cửa sổ dòng lệnh cho quản trị viên.  Chi tiết được định nghĩa trong tập tin cấu hình <filename>/etc/rsyslog.conf</filename> (được hướng dẫn trong trang hướng dẫn sử dụng có cùng tên)."

msgid "Certain C functions, which are specialized in sending logs, simplify the use of the <command>rsyslogd</command> daemon. However some daemons manage their own log files (this is the case, for example, of <command>samba</command>, that implements Windows shares on Linux)."
msgstr "Một vài hàm C, vốn chuyên để gửi đi các thông điệp nhật ký, đơn giản hóa việc sử dụng dịch vụ nền <command>rsyslogd</command>. Tuy nhiên, một vài dịch vụ nền quản lý các tập tin nhật ký riêng của chúng (đây là trường hợp, ví dụ, của <command>samba</command>, vốn hiện thực hóa các chia sẻ Windows trên Linux)."

msgid "Note that when <command>systemd</command> is in use, the logs are actually collected by <command>systemd</command> before being forwarded to <command>rsyslogd</command>. They are thus also available via <command>systemd</command>'s journal and can be consulted with <command>journalctl</command> (see <xref linkend=\"sect.systemd\" /> for details)."
msgstr "Ghi chú rằng khi <command>systemd</command> đang hoạt động, các thông điệp nhật ký được thu thập bởi <command>systemd</command> trước khi được chuyển tới <command>rsyslogd</command>. Vì thế chúng cũng có thể được truy cập thông qua nhật ký <command>systemd</command> và có thể tham khảo với <command>journalctl</command> (xem <xref linkend=\"sect.systemd\" /> để biết thêm chi tiết)."

msgid "<emphasis>BACK TO BASICS</emphasis> Daemon"
msgstr "<emphasis>TRỞ VỀ CƠ BẢN</emphasis> Dịch vụ chạy nền"

msgid "<primary>daemon</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>dịch vụ chạy nền</primary>"

msgid "A daemon is a program that is not explicitly invoked by the user and that stays in the background, waiting for a certain condition to be met before performing a task. Many server programs are daemons, a term that explains that the letter “d” is frequently present at the end of their name (<command>sshd</command>, <command>smtpd</command>, <command>httpd</command>, etc.)."
msgstr "Một dịch vụ chạy nền là một chương trình không được khởi động trực tiếp bởi người sử dụng và tiếp tục chạy nền, chờ cho một điều kiện nào đó được thỏa để thực hiện một tác vụ. Nhiều chương trình máy phục vụ là các dịch vụ chạy nền, một cụm từ giải thích tốt hơn là ký tự “d” thường xuất hiện ở cuối tên của chúng (<command>sshd</command>, <command>smtpd</command>, <command>httpd</command>, vâng vâng)."

msgid "As a preventive operation, the administrator should regularly read the most relevant server logs. They can thus diagnose problems before they are even reported by disgruntled users. Indeed users may sometimes wait for a problem to occur repeatedly over several days before reporting it. In many cases, there are specific tools to analyze the contents of the larger log files. In particular, such utilities exist for web servers (such as <command>analog</command>, <command>awstats</command>, <command>webalizer</command> for Apache), for FTP servers, for proxy/cache servers, for firewalls, for e-mail servers, for DNS servers, and even for print servers. Some of these utilities operate in a modular manner and allow analysis of several types of log files. This is the case of <command>lire</command>. Other tools, such as <command>logcheck</command> (a software discussed in <xref linkend=\"security\" />), scan these files in search of alerts to be dealt with."
msgstr "Như là một biện pháp phòng chống, quản trị viên nên thường xuyên đọc những nhật ký máy phục vụ có liên quan nhất. Chúng có thể giúp chẩn đoán được các vấn đề trước khi chúng bị báo cáo bởi các người sử dụng đầy giận dữ. Thực vậy, những người sử dụng có thể thỉnh thoảng chờ để một vấn đề xảy ra lặp đi lặp lại qua vài ngày trước khi báo cáo nó. Trong nhiều trường hợp, có nhiều công cụ cụ thể để phân tích nội dung của các tập tin nhật ký lớn hơn. Cụ thể hơn, các tiện ích này tồn tại cho các máy phục vụ web (như là <command>analog</command>, <command>awstats</command>, <command>webalizer</command> cho Apache), cho các máy phục vụ FTP, cho các máy phục vụ trạm chuyển hướng(proxy)/bộ nhớ tạm(cache), cho các tường lửa, cho các máy phục vụ thư điện tử, cho các máy phục vụ DNS, và thậm chí cho các máy phục vụ in ấn. Một số trong những tiện ích trên hoạt động dựa trên nhiều mô-đun và cho phép phân tích nhiều loại tập tin nhật ký. Đây là trường hợp của <command>lire</command>. Các công cụ khác, như là <command>logcheck</command> (một phần mềm được thảo luận ở <xref linkend=\"security\" />), quét qua các tập tin này để tìm kiếm các cảnh báo và xử lý chúng."

